Give me 5 minutes with that Honda and I'll get it down the track in low 11/high 10 seconds. I mean, this combo has been done so much everyone knows the approximate potential with good setup. They couldn't achieve a good setup with what they had, but I feel the car still had high 10s in it.


As for the Lexus... when you spray and the thing gets slower, that's a big hint something is off that a little timing won't fix. I'd like to tinker with it a bit. My knee jerk reaction is to think it's lean, or the fuel is not atomizing properly.
